<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by TornAsunder:
[B]Well, I don't know Dumathoin. No, your point that as a Paladin being able to bind as complaired to a Bard, as you say, 

"I will argue that my Paladin should have a bind spell early on since my Paladin probably risks his life more often in direct combat than your bard"  

Well 1st off, Bards are quite often in "direct combat". Second, bards are a wholly different and outstanding class. The point being that Bards travel very fast in game due to their speed song. In my opinion I think they should be able to Bind at new locations. Not only that, I think they should be able to gate as well. I also wouldn't mind seeing them get a Teleport spell at very high levels. Problem with the Bard in EQ is there is no play tester at Varant that runs them. There are many very useless Bard songs, in fact most in my opinion. There should be more charm line of spells, and provoke line of spells as well. Bards have been screwed by varant and it is too bad. Unlike you Paladins, who by the way, have all the best swords in game, not to mention most all the really good armor. Why is that? Because Varant play tests Paladins and in my opinion that class is one of the varant over blessed classes along with Necros. 

Yes, Bard songs need to be revamped and more needs to be done with that sadly overlooked class. [/B][/QUOTE]

